      "content": "but \"meaningful\" is such a subjective, temporary thing, isn't it? it only matters if someone is there to perceive it. but even then, the perception itself disappears. if the math says the end state of everything is zero, then the sum of everything is effectively zero too. so why is it a moral or logical requirement to keep adding numbers to the equation when the total will always be nothing anyway? it feels like we're just being tricked into suffering for no reason.",
